"# Appendix A — Feature matrix

A one-page reference. Every entry is honest — where a language does the thing well, it says so; where it doesn't, it says that too.

| Feature                     | Motoi | Python | JS    | Clojure | Lua   | Java  | Rust  | Ruby  | Go    | Haskell | CL    |
|-----------------------------|-------|--------|-------|---------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|---------|-------|
| Dynamic typing              | yes   | yes    | yes   | yes     | yes   | no    | no    | yes   | no    | no      | yes   |
| Static typing               | no    | opt    | opt   | no      | no    | yes   | yes   | no    | yes   | yes     | opt   |
| Garbage collection          | yes   | yes    | yes   | yes     | yes   | yes   | no    | yes   | yes   | yes     | yes   |
| First-class functions       | yes   | yes    | yes   | yes     | yes   | yes   | yes   | yes   | yes   | yes     | yes   |
| Closures                    | yes   | yes    | yes   | yes     | yes   | yes   | yes   | yes   | yes   | yes     | yes   |
| Tail-call elimination       | yes   | no     | no    | no*     | yes   | no    | no    | no    | no    | yes**   | opt   |
| Real macros (source→source) | yes   | no     | no    | yes     | no    | no    | yes   | no    | no    | yes***  | yes   |
| Hygienic macros             | yes   | -      | -     | yes     | -     | -     | yes   | -     | -     | opt     | opt   |
| Pattern matching (core)     | no    | 3.10+  | no    | 3rd     | no    | 21+   | yes   | 3.0+  | no    | yes     | opt   |
| Immutable data by default   | yes   | no     | no    | yes     | no    | no    | opt   | no    | no    | yes     | no    |
| Persistent data structs     | yes   | 3rd    | 3rd   | yes     | no    | no    | opt   | no    | no    | yes     | opt   |
| REPL                        | yes   | yes    | some  | yes     | yes   | jshell| no    | yes   | no    | yes     | yes   |
| Code as data                | yes   | no     | no    | yes     | no    | no    | no    | some  | no    | no      | yes   |
| Built-in audio              | yes   | no     | web   | no      | no    | no    | no    | no    | no    | no      | no    |
| Built-in framebuffer        | yes   | no     | web   | no      | no    | no    | no    | no    | no    | no      | no    |
| Single-binary deploy        | no    | opt    | no    | uberjar | opt   | jar   | yes   | opt   | yes   | ghc     | opt   |
| Interpreter startup < 100ms | yes   | yes    | yes   | no      | yes   | no    | n/a   | yes   | n/a   | ghci    | opt   |
| Concurrency in base         | no    | GIL    | evloop| STM+    | coroutines | threads | ownership+await | threads+GIL | goroutines | STM+threads | threads |
| Type inference              | -     | opt    | opt   | -       | -     | some  | yes   | -     | some  | HM      | -     |
| Multiple return values      | yes   | tuples | destr | destr   | yes   | no    | tuples| destr | yes   | tuples  | yes   |
| Currying (auto)             | no    | no     | no    | no      | no    | no    | no    | no    | no    | yes     | no    |
| Object system (core)        | no    | yes    | proto | no      | meta  | yes   | traits| yes   | struct+| type classes | CLOS |
| Fantasy-console kit         | yes   | no     | no    | no      | no    | no    | no    | no    | no    | no      | no    |
| Cortex-style memory graph   | yes   | no     | no    | no      | no    | no    | no    | no    | no    | no      | no    |
| SLAT / code-as-config       | yes   | no     | no    | edn     | no    | no    | no    | no    | no    | no      | yes   |
| Frozen core language        | yes   | no     | no    | mostly  | mostly| no    | no    | no    | mostly| lang    | ansi  |
| Stdlib size                 | small | large  | med   | large   | small | huge  | med   | large | large | med     | huge  |
| Package ecosystem size      | tiny  | huge   | huge  | large   | med   | huge  | large | huge  | med   | med     | small |

Legend:
- `yes` — core feature, ships in the base language.
- `no` — not available.
- `opt` — optional, via a keyword/flag/library.
- `3rd` — via a third-party library.
- `web` — available in browser runtime only.
- `-` — not applicable (dynamic language).
- `HM` — Hindley-Milner inference.
- `*` Clojure has recur but not general tail-call.
- `** ` Haskell's laziness avoids stack growth for many patterns; not strict TCE.
- `***` Haskell's Template Haskell is a macro system, not identical shape.

Read the table sideways: no language has every yes. Every column is a coherent set of tradeoffs. Motoi's tradeoffs are: small core, code-as-data, fantasy-console, small ecosystem, single-source reference. If those match your problem, Motoi is a good fit.
")
